SWT (Eclipse Standard Widget Toolkit) is an open source widget toolkit
for Java designed to provide efficient, portable access to the
user-interface facilities of the operating systems on which it
is implemented.

This build script packages the pre-compiled SWT library components
needed by Java applications like Angry IP Scanner or Eclipse.

Please note that it only supports 64-bit systems (x86_64).
32-bit architectures are not supported by the upstream developer
for this version.

A Java Runtime Environment (such as openjdk or zulu-openjdk) is 
required to use this library.
